title: Cape Streten
text: Cape Streten () is an ice cape at the northeast tip of <a href="Sakellari%20Peninsula">Sakellari Peninsula</a>, forming the west side of the entrance to <a href="Amundsen%20Bay">Amundsen Bay</a>. Plotted from air photos taken by ANARE (<a href="Australian%20National%20Antarctic%20Research%20Expeditions">Australian National Antarctic Research Expeditions</a>) in November 1956. Named by <a href="Antarctic%20Names%20Committee%20of%20Australia">Antarctic Names Committee of Australia</a> (ANCA) for <a href="Neil%20Anthony%20Streten">Neil Anthony Streten</a>, meteorologist at <a href="Mawson%20Station">Mawson Station</a> in 1960.
